{# Reusable metric summary header.

   Two renderings, switched on `metric_name` (set only on metric
   DETAIL pages, not dashboard tiles):

   - Detail page → a boxed brand-accented strip, mirroring the
     work-item lifecycle metric strip: uppercase label + the
     one-line headline. The breadcrumb already carries the
     metric name, so the strip is the at-a-glance summary.
   - Dashboard tile → the lighter title + headline (no box;
     five of these stacked would be visually heavy).

   Required context:
     summary.title    — short metric name, e.g. "Cycle time"
     summary.headline — one-line statement, e.g.
                         "43 items completed · P50 0.1d · P85 1.4d · P95 7.8d"
#}
{% if metric_name %}
  <div class="metric-strip">
    <span class="metric-strip-label">{{ summary.title }}</span>
    <span class="metric-strip-headline">{{ summary.headline }}</span>
  </div>
{% else %}
  <div class="metric-summary">
    {# H3 (subsection), not H2 (eyebrow). H2 in the Knox design
       system is UPPERCASE — wrong for a metric name like "Cycle
       time". #}
    <h3 class="metric-summary-title">{{ summary.title }}</h3>
    <p class="metric-summary-headline">{{ summary.headline }}</p>
  </div>
{% endif %}
